<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: One of my latest character has been killed by a mana ball trap on a chest (i know it's lame, but...), but in the Hall of Fame the cause of death is left blank. <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: All bolt and ball traps on chests behave similarily. The code in traps.c handles traps on chests and on the floor similarily when calling the damaging function:  who = -2 in both cases and the code in spells1.c sets the string killer only correctly for the floor traps: 
<pre>if (who == -2)
{
        sprintf(killer, t_name + t_info[cave[p_ptr-&gt;py][p_ptr-&gt;px].t_idx].name);
}
</pre>
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


